57.1	Walker_Percy	Walker Percy	Walker Percy (May 28, 1916 â€“ May 10, 1990) was an American Southern author whose interests included philosophy and semiotics. Percy is known for his philosophical novels set in and around New Orleans, Louisiana, the first of which, The Moviegoer, won the U.S. National Book Award for Fiction. He devoted his literary life to the exploration of "the dislocation of man in the modern age." His work displays a unique combination of existential questioning, Southern sensibility, and deep Catholic faith.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/c3/W_Percy.jpg/220px-W_Percy.jpg
